cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SD, cs.DL, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of model-driven development to microservices, which is a software engineering topic. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as microservices are a distributed system architecture. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of implementing microservices and proposes a solution using model-driven development. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a survey of relevant characteristics of collaborative model-driven software engineering. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the implementation of microservices and the potential use of model-driven development to reduce accidental complexity.
